      <learningContent>
        <title></title>
        <lcInstruction>
          <description>
            <para>Component Location and Function</para>
            <para>Electro-Optic Identification Device</para>
            <para>
              <randomList>
                <listItem>
                  <para>The EOID module replaces the VSS in the EOID configuration, and provides a laser-induced differential absorption radar technology to identify mine-like objects.</para>
                  <para>
                    <randomList>
                      <listItem>
                        <para>The EOID has a transmit window and two receive windows.</para>
                      </listItem>
                    </randomList>
                  </para>
                </listItem>
              </randomList>
            </para>
            <figure>
              <title></title>
              <graphic infoEntityIdent="ICN-ANAQS20A-AA-ZG3A60000-N-61331-0025-A-000-01" />
            </figure>
            <para>Theory of Operation</para>
            <para>Electro-Optic Identification Device</para>
            <para>The EOID assembly is a fit and form replacement for the VSS assembly, however, it performs a different function. The EOID uses laser light to scan the seabed and create an image. It performs target cueing of objects found in the seabed.</para>
            <figure>
              <title></title>
              <graphic infoEntityIdent="ICN-ANAQS20A-AA-ZG3A60000-N-61331-0025-A-000-01" />
            </figure>
            <para>Theory of Operation</para>
            <para>Electro-Optic Identification Device (continued)</para>
            <para>
              <randomList>
                <listItem>
                  <para>Range, contrast, and target cueing data are provided to the towed body.</para>
                </listItem>
                <listItem>
                  <para>The EOID is comprised of a laser assembly that creates the light signal. The light is propagated to the water after a fan of light beams is created in the beam diverger.</para>
                </listItem>
                <listItem>
                  <para>The Data Processor (DP) provides image processing. The System Control Communications (SCC) interfaces with the Ethernet Switch for communications with the towed body as well as provides executive control over the EOID.</para>
                </listItem>
                <listItem>
                  <para>The hardware controller also provides control for the EOID by enabling and disabling hardware at the appropriate times.</para>
                </listItem>
                <listItem>
                  <para>The EOID is a class 4 laser and presents a personnel hazard for anyone looking directly into the beam or specular reflection. Because of this hazard, interlocks have been incorporated into the EOID that prevents EOID firing when the towed body is not submerged in water.</para>
                </listItem>
              </randomList>
            </para>
          </description>
        </lcInstruction>
